原创： 曾健明 生信技能树
2017-09-22

这个一个肿瘤外显子项目的文章发表并且公布的公共数据，我这里给出全套分析流程代码。只需要你肯实践，就可以运行成功。

文章解读

paper；https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4812767/ a whole-exome sequencing (WES) study was performed in 161 NPC cases and 895 controls of Southern Chinese descent

测序概述：

We sequenced the blood samples from 161 NPC cases, including 39 EAO cases, 63 FH+ cases from 52 independent families, and 59 sporadic cases by WES and achieved an average coverage of 49-fold on target (range of 32- to 76-fold)

后来还扩大了验证样本集：

An additional 2,160 NPC cases and 2,433 healthy controls from Hong Kong were further examined for the selected candidate variants.

数据全部上传了：

Whole-exome sequencing data for the early-age onset cases have been deposited in the Sequence Read Archive (SRA) database (accession ID SRA291701).

了解WES数据分析步骤： 2016-A Survey of Computational Tools to Analyze and Interpret Whole Exome Sequencing Data

从SRA数据库下载并转换为fastq测序数据文件

把上面的描述文本存为文件npc.sra.txt下载脚本如下：

  1. cat npc.sra.txt | cut -f 4|while read id
  2. do echo $id
  3. wget -c ftp://ftp-trace.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sra/sra-instant/reads/ByStudy/sra/SRP/SRP035/SRP035573/$id/$id.sra
  4. done

转换脚本如下:

  1. cat npc.sra.txt | while read id
  2. do
  3. array=($id)
  4. echo  ${array[3]}.sra  ${array[7]} 
  5. ~/biosoft/sratoolkit/sratoolkit.2.8.2-1-centos_linux64/bin/fastq-dump --gzip --split-3 -A \  
  6. ${array[7]}  ${array[3]}.sra 
  7. done

  1. ls *.gz |xargs ~/biosoft/fastqc/FastQC/fastqc -o ./ -t 5

然后走WES的标准SNP-calling流程

选用的是经典的GATK best practice的流程，代码如下:

  1. module load java/1.8.0_91
  2. GENOME=/home/jianmingzeng/reference/genome/human_g1k_v37/human_g1k_v37.fasta
  3. INDEX=/home/jianmingzeng/reference/index/bwa/human_g1k_v37
  4. GATK=/home/jianmingzeng/biosoft/GATK/GenomeAnalysisTK.jar
  5. PICARD=/home/jianmingzeng/biosoft/picardtools/2.9.2/picard.jar
  7. DBSNP=/home/jianmingzeng/annotation/variation/human/dbSNP/All_20160601.vcf.gz
  8. SNP=/home/jianmingzeng/biosoft/GATK/resources/bundle/b37/1000G_phase1.snps.high_confidence.b37.vcf.gz
  9. INDEL=/home/jianmingzeng/biosoft/GATK/resources/bundle/b37/Mills_and_1000G_gold_standard.indels.b37.vcf.gz
  11. KG_SNP=/home/jianmingzeng/biosoft/GATK/resources/bundle/b37/1000G_phase1.snps.high_confidence.b37.vcf.gz
  12. Mills_indels=/home/jianmingzeng/biosoft/GATK/resources/bundle/b37/Mills_and_1000G_gold_standard.indels.b37.vcf
  13. KG_indels=/home/jianmingzeng/biosoft/GATK/resources/bundle/b37/1000G_phase1.indels.b37.vcf
  15. TMPDIR=/home/jianmingzeng/tmp/software
  16. ## samtools and bwa are in the environment
  17. ## samtools Version: 1.3.1 (using htslib 1.3.1)
  18. ## bwa Version: 0.7.15-r1140
  21. #arr=($1)
  22. #fq1=${arr[0]}
  23. #fq2=${arr[1]}
  24. #sample=${arr[2]}
  26. fq1=$1
  27. fq2=$2
  28. sample=$3
  31. #####################################################
  32. ################ Step 1 : Alignment #################
  33. #####################################################
  34. start=$(date +%s.%N)
  35. echo bwa `date`
  36. bwa mem -t 5 -M  -R "@RG\tID:$sample\tSM:$sample\tLB:WES\tPL:Illumina" $INDEX $fq1 $fq2 1>$sample.sam 2>/dev/null 
  37. echo bwa `date`
  38. dur=$(echo "$(date +%s.%N) - $start" | bc)
  39. printf "Execution time for BWA : %.6f seconds" $dur
  40. echo 
  42. #####################################################
  43. ################ Step 2: Sort and Index #############
  44. #####################################################
  45. start=$(date +%s.%N)
  46. echo SortSam `date`
  47. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR    -Xmx40g -jar $PICARD SortSam SORT_ORDER=coordinate INPUT=$sample.sam OUTPUT=$sample.bam
  48. samtools index $sample.bam
  49. echo SortSam `date`
  50. dur=$(echo "$(date +%s.%N) - $start" | bc)
  51. printf "Execution time for SortSam : %.6f seconds" $dur
  52. echo 
  53. rm $sample.sam 
  55. #####################################################
  56. ################ Step 3: Basic Statistics ###########
  57. #####################################################
  58. start=$(date +%s.%N)
  59. echo stats `date`
  60. samtools flagstat $sample.bam > ${sample}.alignment.flagstat
  61. samtools stats  $sample.bam > ${sample}.alignment.stat
  62. echo plot-bamstats -p ${sample}_QC  ${sample}.alignment.stat
  63. echo stats `date`
  64. dur=$(echo "$(date +%s.%N) - $start" | bc)
  65. printf "Execution time for Basic Statistics : %.6f seconds" $dur
  66. echo 
  68. #####################################################
  69. ####### Step 4: multiple filtering for bam files ####
  70. #####################################################
  73. ###MarkDuplicates###
  74. start=$(date +%s.%N)
  75. echo MarkDuplicates `date`
  76. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR    -Xmx40g -jar $PICARD MarkDuplicates \
  77. INPUT=$sample.bam OUTPUT=${sample}_marked.bam METRICS_FILE=$sample.metrics
  78. echo MarkDuplicates `date`
  79. dur=$(echo "$(date +%s.%N) - $start" | bc)
  80. printf "Execution time for MarkDuplicates : %.6f seconds" $dur
  81. echo 
  82. rm $sample.bam  
  84. ###FixMateInfo###
  85. start=$(date +%s.%N)
  86. echo FixMateInfo `date`
  87. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR    -Xmx40g -jar $PICARD FixMateInformation \
  88. INPUT=${sample}_marked.bam OUTPUT=${sample}_marked_fixed.bam SO=coordinate
  89. samtools index ${sample}_marked_fixed.bam
  90. echo FixMateInfo `date`
  91. dur=$(echo "$(date +%s.%N) - $start" | bc)
  92. printf "Execution time for FixMateInfo  : %.6f seconds" $dur
  93. echo 
  96. rm ${sample}_marked.bam 
  98. #####################################################
  99. ####### Step 5: gatk process bam files ##############
  100. #####################################################
  104. ### SplitNCigar ###
  105. start=$(date +%s.%N)
  106. echo SplitNCigar `date`
  107. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g -jar $GATK -T SplitNCigarReads \
  108.  -R $GENOME  -I ${sample}_marked_fixed.bam  -o ${sample}_marked_fixed_split.bam \
  109. -rf ReassignOneMappingQuality -RMQF 255 -RMQT 60 -U ALLOW_N_CIGAR_READS 
  110. #--fix_misencoded_quality_scores
  111. ## --fix_misencoded_quality_scores only if phred 64 
  112. echo SplitNCigar `date`
  113. dur=$(echo "$(date +%s.%N) - $start" | bc)
  114. printf "Execution time for SplitNCigar : %.6f seconds" $dur
  115. echo 
  117. rm ${sample}_marked_fixed.bam 
  118. # rm ${sample}.sam ${sample}.bam ${sample}_marked.bam ${sample}_marked_fixed.bam
  121. ###RealignerTargetCreator###
  122. start=$(date +%s.%N)
  123. echo RealignerTargetCreator `date`
  124. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g -jar $GATK -T RealignerTargetCreator \
  125. -I ${sample}_marked_fixed_split.bam -R $GENOME -o ${sample}_target.intervals \
  126. -known $Mills_indels -known $KG_indels -nt 5
  127. echo RealignerTargetCreator `date`
  128. dur=$(echo "$(date +%s.%N) - $start" | bc)
  129. printf "Execution time for RealignerTargetCreator : %.6f seconds" $dur
  130. echo 
  133. ###IndelRealigner###
  134. start=$(date +%s.%N)
  135. echo IndelRealigner `date`
  136. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g -jar $GATK -T IndelRealigner \
  137. -I ${sample}_marked_fixed_split.bam  -R $GENOME -targetIntervals ${sample}_target.intervals \
  138. -o ${sample}_realigned.bam -known $Mills_indels -known $KG_indels
  139. echo IndelRealigner `date`
  140. dur=$(echo "$(date +%s.%N) - $start" | bc)
  141. printf "Execution time for IndelRealigner : %.6f seconds" $dur
  142. echo 
  144. rm ${sample}_marked_fixed_split.bam
  146. ###BaseRecalibrator###
  147. start=$(date +%s.%N)
  148. echo BaseRecalibrator `date`
  149. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g -jar $GATK -T BaseRecalibrator \
  150. -I ${sample}_realigned.bam -R $GENOME -o ${sample}_temp.table -knownSites $DBSNP
  151. echo BaseRecalibrator `date`
  152. dur=$(echo "$(date +%s.%N) - $start" | bc)
  153. printf "Execution time for BaseRecalibrator : %.6f seconds" $dur
  154. echo 
  157. ###PrintReads###
  158. start=$(date +%s.%N)
  159. echo PrintReads `date`
  160. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g -jar $GATK -T PrintReads \
  161. -R $GENOME -I ${sample}_realigned.bam -o ${sample}_recal.bam -BQSR ${sample}_temp.table
  162. samtools index ${sample}_recal.bam
  163. echo PrintReads `date`
  164. dur=$(echo "$(date +%s.%N) - $start" | bc)
  165. printf "Execution time for PrintReads : %.6f seconds" $dur
  166. echo 
  168. rm  ${sample}_realigned.bam
  169. chmod uga=r   ${sample}_recal.bam 
  171. #####################################################
  172. ############## Step 6: gatk call snp/indel##########
  173. #####################################################
  175. ### 
  176. start=$(date +%s.%N)
  177. echo HaplotypeCaller `date`
  178. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g -jar $GATK -T HaplotypeCaller  \
  179. -R $GENOME -I ${sample}_recal.bam --dbsnp $DBSNP  \
  180. -stand_emit_conf 10 -o  ${sample}_raw.snps.indels.vcf
  181. echo HaplotypeCaller `date`
  182. dur=$(echo "$(date +%s.%N) - $start" | bc)
  183. printf "Execution time for HaplotypeCaller : %.6f seconds" $dur
  184. echo 
  187. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g -jar $GATK -T SelectVariants  -R $GENOME  \
  188. -selectType SNP \
  189. -V ${sample}_raw.snps.indels.vcf -o ${sample}_raw_snps.vcf
  191. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g -jar $GATK -T SelectVariants  -R $GENOME \
  192. -selectType INDEL  \
  193. -V ${sample}_raw.snps.indels.vcf   -o ${sample}_raw_indels.vcf
  196. ## 
  197. :'
  198. '
  199. ## for SNP
  201. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g -jar $GATK -T VariantFiltration -R $GENOME  \
  202. --filterExpression "QD < 2.0 || FS > 60.0 || MQ < 40.0 || MQRankSum < -12.5 || ReadPosRankSum < -8.0"  \
  203. --filterName "my_snp_filter" \
  204. -V ${sample}_raw_snps.vcf  -o ${sample}_filtered_snps.vcf   
  206. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g -jar $GATK -T SelectVariants -R $GENOME  \
  207. --excludeFiltered \
  208. -V ${sample}_filtered_snps.vcf  -o  ${sample}_filtered_PASS.snps.vcf
  211. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g -jar $GATK -T VariantEval -R $GENOME  \
  212. -eval ${sample}_filtered_PASS.snps.vcf -o  ${sample}_filtered_PASS.snps.vcf.eval
  215. ## for  INDEL
  218. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g -jar $GATK -T VariantFiltration -R $GENOME  \
  219. --filterExpression "QD < 2.0 || FS > 200.0 || ReadPosRankSum < -20.0"  \
  220. --filterName "my_indel_filter" \
  221. -V ${sample}_raw_indels.vcf  -o ${sample}_filtered_indels.vcf   
  223. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g -jar $GATK -T SelectVariants -R $GENOME  \
  224. --excludeFiltered \
  225. -V ${sample}_filtered_indels.vcf  -o  ${sample}_filtered_PASS.indels.vcf
  227. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g -jar $GATK -T VariantEval -R $GENOME  \
  228. -eval ${sample}_filtered_PASS.indels.vcf -o  ${sample}_filtered_PASS.indels.vcf.eval

然后走走somatic mutation calling流程

因为是配对数据，还可以走somatic mutation calling流程

  1. reference=/home/jianmingzeng/reference/genome/human_g1k_v37/human_g1k_v37.fasta
  2. GENOME=/home/jianmingzeng/reference/genome/human_g1k_v37/human_g1k_v37.fasta
  3. TMPDIR=/home/jianmingzeng/tmp/software
  4. normal_bam=NPC10F-N_recal.bam
  5. tumor_bam=NPC10F-T_recal.bam
  6. sample=NPC10F
  8. #####################################################
  9. ################### Step : Run VarScan #############
  10. #####################################################
  11. normal_pileup="samtools mpileup -q 1 -f $reference $normal_bam";
  12. tumor_pileup="samtools mpileup -q 1 -f $reference $tumor_bam";
  13. # Next, issue a system call that pipes input from these commands into VarScan :
  14. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g  -jar ~/biosoft/VarScan/VarScan.v2.3.9.jar \
  15. somatic <($normal_pileup) <($tumor_pileup) $sample
  16. java -jar ~/biosoft/VarScan/VarScan.v2.3.9.jar processSomatic $sample.snp
  18. #####################################################
  19. ################### Step : Run Mutect2 #############
  20. ##################################################### 
  21. java -Djava.io.tmpdir=$TMPDIR   -Xmx40g -jar $GATK  -T MuTect2 \
  22. -R $GENOME -I:tumor $tumor_bam  -I:normal $normal_bam \
  23. --dbsnp  $DBSNP   -o ${sample}-mutect2.vcf
  25. #####################################################
  26. ################### Step : Run Muse#################
  27. #####################################################
  28. ~/biosoft/muse/muse call -O $sample -f $reference $tumor_bam $normal_bam
  29. ~/biosoft/muse/muse sump -I ${sample}.MuSE.txt -E –O ${sample}.vcf –D $DBSNP

其中varscan耗费两个半小时，结果如下：

  1. 893539210 positions in tumor
  2. 891822458 positions shared in normal
  3. 79827518 had sufficient coverage for comparison
  4. 79718238 were called Reference

  6. 102492 were called Germline

  14. 101352 VarScan calls processed
  15. 2342 were Somatic (556 high confidence)
  16. 95144 were Germline (4830 high confidence)
  17. 3502 were LOH (3484 high confidence)

这3个软件找到的somatic mutation可以互相对比一下，差异主要是在哪里，都值得自己去探究，这样最终确定的肿瘤外显子测序数据分析流程就更有把握。
